README.md
     1→# Tock
     5→[Features](#features) • [Quick Start](#quick-start) • [Commands](#commands) •
     6→[Configuration](#configuration) • [Theme](#theme) • [File Format](#file-format) • [Shell](#shell-completion) • [Inspiration](#inspiration) • [License](#license)
     7→
     8→## Features
    12→**Tock** is a powerful time tracking tool for the command line. It saves activity logs as plaintext files and provides an interactive terminal UI for viewing your time.
    13→
    14→Features include:
    15→
    16→- 📝 **Simple plaintext format** - Activities stored in human-readable files
    17→- 📅 **Notes & Tags** - Attach detailed notes and tags to activities
    18→- 🎨 **Interactive TUI** - Beautiful terminal calendar view using Bubble Tea
    19→- ⚡ **Fast & Lightweight** - Single binary, no dependencies
    20→- 🔄 **Compatible** - Reads/writes Bartib file format and TimeWarrior data files
    21→- 🎨 **Customizable Themes** - Multiple color themes and custom color support
    22→- 📅 **iCal Export** - Generate .ics files for calendar integration, or sync with system calendars (macOS only)
    23→
    24→<hr clear="right"/>
