   316→#### 12-Hour Format Examples
   328→#### 24-Hour Format (Default)
   343→## Commands
   345→```bash
   346→
   347→A simple timetracker for the command line
   348→
   349→Usage:
   350→  tock [command]
   351→
   352→Available Commands:
   353→  add         Add a completed activity
   354→  analyze     Analyze your productivity patterns
   355→  calendar    Show interactive calendar view
   356→  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
   357→  continue    Continues a previous activity
   358→  current     Lists all currently running activities
   359→  help        Help about any command
   360→  ical        Generate iCal (.ics) file for a specific task, all tasks in a day, or all tasks
   361→  last        List recent unique activities
   362→  list        List activities (Calendar View)
   363→  remove      Remove an activity
   364→  report      Generate time tracking report
   365→  start       Start a new activity
   366→  stop        Stop the current activity
   367→  version     Print the version info
   368→  watch       Display a full-screen stopwatch for the current activity
   369→
   370→Flags:
   371→  -b, --backend string   Storage backend: 'file' (default) or 'timewarrior'
   372→      --config string    Config file directory (default is $HOME/.config/tock/tock.yaml)
   373→  -f, --file string      Path to the activity log file (or data directory for timewarrior)
   374→  -h, --help             help for tock
   375→  -v, --version          version for tock
   376→Use "tock [command] --help" for more information about a command.
   377→```
   378→
   379→[**→ Commands Reference**](docs/commands.md)
